h: 56\u00f77=8.)"},{"id":"n2_13","inst":"Choose the correct answer.","txt":"Arrange in order from smallest: 0.45, 3/8, 42%","opts":["3/8, 42%, 0.45","42%, 3/8, 0.45","3/8, 0.45, 42%"],"cor":0,"exp":"3/8=0.375, 42%=0.42, 0.45. Order: 0.375, 0.42, 0.45."},{"id":"n2_14","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is 2\u00b3?","opts":["6","8","16"],"cor":1,"exp":"2\u00b3 = 2\u00d72\u00d72 = 8."}],"3":[{"id":"n3_1","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is 2.5 \u00d7 10\u00b3?","opts":["250","2500","25000"],"cor":1,"exp":"10\u00b3 = 1000. 2.5 \u00d7 1000 = 2500."},{"id":"n3_2","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Express 0.00045 in standard form.","opts":["4.5 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2074","45 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2075","4.5 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b3"],"cor":0,"exp":"Move decimal 4 places right: 4.5 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2074."},{"id":"n3_3","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is \u00b3\u221a27?","opts":["3","9","27"],"cor":0,"exp":"3 \u00d7 3 \u00d7 3 = 27. So the cube root of 27 is 3."},{"id":"n3_4","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Simplify: (2x\u00b3)\u00b2","opts":["2x\u2076","4x\u2076","4x\u2075"],"cor":1,"exp":"(2x\u00b3)\u00b2 = 2\u00b2 \u00d7 (x\u00b3)\u00b2 = 4 \u00d7 x\u2076 = 4x\u2076."},{"id":"n3_5","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is 3/7 \u00f7 2/5?","opts":["6/35","15/14","5/14"],"cor":1,"exp":"Dividing by a fraction: flip and multiply. 3/7 \u00d7 5/2 = 15/14."},{"id":"n3_6","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Increase \u00a380 by 12.5%.","opts":["\u00a385","\u00a390","\u00a392.50"],"cor":1,"exp":"12.5% of 80 = 10. \u00a380 + \u00a310 = \u00a390."},{"id":"n3_7","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is (-2)\u00b3?","opts":["6","-6","-8"],"cor":2,"exp":"(-2)\u00b3 = (-2)\u00d7(-2)\u00d7(-2) = 4\u00d7(-2) = -8. Odd power keeps negative."},{"id":"n3_8","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Simplify: \u221a50","opts":["5\u221a2","2\u221a5","25\u221a2"],"cor":0,"exp":"\u221a50 = \u221a(25\u00d72) = \u221a25 \u00d7 \u221a2 = 5\u221a2."},{"id":"n3_9","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is 0.6 recurring as a fraction?","opts":["3/5","2/3","6/10"],"cor":1,"exp":"Let x=0.666... 10x=6.666... 10x-x=6. 9x=6. x=6/9=2/3."},{"id":"n3_10","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Rationalise the denominator: 1/\u221a3","opts":["\u221a3/3","3/\u221a3","1/3"],"cor":0,"exp":"Multiply top and bottom by \u221a3: (1\u00d7\u221a3)/(\u221a3\u00d7\u221a3) = \u221a3/3."},{"id":"n3_11","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is (3 \u00d7 10\u2074) \u00d7 (2 \u00d7 10\u00b3)?","opts":["6 \u00d7 10\u2077","5 \u00d7 10\u2077","6 \u00d7 10\u00b9\u00b2"],"cor":0,"exp":"3\u00d72=6. 10\u2074\u00d710\u00b3=10\u2077. Answer: 6\u00d710\u2077."},{"id":"n3_12","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"What is 2\u207b\u00b3?","opts":["1/6","1/8","-8"],"cor":1,"exp":"2\u207b\u00b3 = 1/2\u00b3 = 1/8. A negative power means 'one over'."},{"id":"n3_13","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"A price goes up from \u00a340 to \u00a348. What is the percentage increase?","opts":["8%","15%","20%"],"cor":2,"exp":"Increase = \u00a38. Percentage = (8/40)\u00d7100 = 20%."},{"id":"n3_14","inst":"Calculate.","txt":"Factorise: x\u00b2 - 9","opts":["(x-3)(x+3)","(x-9)(x+1)","(x-3)\u00b2"],"cor":0,"exp":"This is the difference of two squares: x\u00b2-9 = (x-3)(x+3)."}]};

