    {"id":"ser2_1","q":"Read and explain: How does the author use language to persuade the reader? Identify at least 2 techniques.\n\nPassage: Imagine a world without bees. No buzzing in gardens, no golden honey, and — most frighteningly — no pollination of the crops we depend on. A staggering 75% of the world's food crops rely on pollinators. Yet every year, bee populations decline by up to 30%. Can we really afford to ignore this crisis? The time to act is now, before it is too late.","hint":"Look for: rhetorical questions, statistics, emotive language, direct address.","answer":"The author uses: 1) Rhetorical question ('Can we really afford...') to make the reader feel responsible. 2) Statistics ('75%' and '30%') to provide hard evidence. 3) Imperative/urgency ('The time to act is now'). 4) Emotive imagery ('Imagine a world without bees') to create an emotional response.","marks":5}
